</TD>
<TD>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=GREEN>
<B><I>What happens if the SIM card password is entered incorrectly?</I></B></FONT>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=NAVY BLUE>
<P>If an incorrect SIM card password has been entered three times, it would block the SIM card. You would need to enter **05* followed by PUK code to unlock the SIM card. The PUK code can be obtained from your network provider.</P>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=GREEN>
<B><I>How do I setup my WAP access?</I></B></FONT>
<P>To set up the WAP on this handset goto to menu -> Webaccess -> Web Sessions -> select your network provider -> press Menu -> Set Default.
Note: You may need to check with your network provider that WAP is setup on your account.</P>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=GREEN>
<B><I>Does the USB connection charge the phone?</I></B></FONT>
<P>Yes the usb connection will charge the phone, you will need to have the driver installed for this to work. Also if the battery is completly drained it will not charge the phone.</P>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=GREEN>
<B><I>How to do a Master Reset on the handset?</I></B></FONT>
<P>Select Menu button> Settings> Initial Setup> Master Reset> Security Code, input 000000.</P>
<FONT FACE=ARIAL SIZE=2 COLOR=GREEN>
<B><I>How do I unlock the SIM card lock?</I></B></FONT>
<P>The SIM unlock code is set by the service provider, please contacf your service provider for assistance. When activated, the phone when powered on will prompt for the unlock code.</P>
</FONT>
